Interface ToManyIndexedAssociationManager<T,​E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AssociationManager<T,​E>, ToManyAssociationManager<T,​E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractArrayAssociationManager, AbstractListAssociationManager, AbstractToManyIndexedAssociationManager
    public interface ToManyIndexedAssociationManager<T,​E>
extends ToManyAssociationManager<T,​E>
    An object that during view application manages the association between an object and a indexed collection or array composed in the object.
    Author:
    Carl Harris

        Parameters:
        owner - the subject owner
        associateEntity - a view entity representing the state of the associate in the view
        objectFactory - object factory to use to create an instance of the associate if necessary
        Returns:
